3.0  ACCIDENT PREVENTION PROGRAM

Some processes subject to the Risk Management regulation are also subject to the Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) Process Safety Management (PSM) standard.  PSM governs the same processes and regulated substances at the site that are subject to 40 CFR 68.  CCL has a PSM program at the Cumberland facility that includes the following elements:

- Employee Participation;
- Process Safety Information;
- Process Hazards Analysis;
- Operating Procedures;
- Training;
- Contractors;
- Pre-Startup Safety Review;
- Mechanical Integrity;
- Hot Work Permit;
- Management of Change;
- Incident Investigation;
- Emergency Planning and Response; and
- Compliance Audits.

